name: Portage Service Plaza (westbound)
directions: Find the center of the plaza, where you can see most of the big signs saying “food court” and “restrooms” and whatnot. If you’re looking for a unisex bathroom ignore the big sign that says “bathrooms” - those are gendered and multi-stall. Instead, head toward the hallway labeled “trucker lounge”. Immediately on the left is a unisex family restroom with a changing table. It is also wheelchair accessible. Further down the hall, there is a room labeled “trucker lounge and showers”. There are four single-user unisex “trucker designated” (not enforced) restrooms with showers. These are also wheelchair accessible. I’m assuming the conditions are similar for this plaza’s Eastbound equivalent “Brady’s Leap” plaza.
comment: Cleanliness seems generally good.
